INSTALL

Prerequisites:
--------------

 - Perl 5.10+
 - MongoDB 2.2+

Perl Modules:

 - AnyEvent
 - AnyEvent::HTTP
 - Data::Validate::Domain
 - Data::Validate::IP
 - Date::Calc
 - Date::Manip
 - DateTime
 - HTML::Entities
 - HTML::TreeBuilder::XPath
 - JSON
 - List::MoreUtils
 - Lucy
 - Modern::Perl 
 - Mojolicious
 - MongoDB
 - Net::IP::Match::Regexp
 - Net::Twitter
 - String::Truncate
 - Tie::IxHash
 - URI::Encode
 - URI::Escape
 - WWW::Mechanize
 - Mojolicious::Plugin::Bcrypt

Or, in one big CPAN Minus command:

cpanm AnyEvent AnyEvent::HTTP Data::Validate::Domain Data::Validate::IP Date::Calc Date::Manip DateTime HTML::Entities HTML::TreeBuilder::XPath JSON List::MoreUtils Lucy Modern::Perl  Mojolicious MongoDB Net::IP::Match::Regexp Net::Twitter String::Truncate Tie::IxHash URI::Encode URI::Escape WWW::Mechanize Mojolicious::Plugin::Bcrypt

Setting up:
-----------
You need to set up a twitter API key and enter the credentials into the 
bin/fetch-twitter-api.pl script in order for the twitter function to work.